obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (13993)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=13993&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Drugs ^1[and Cosmetics]`
  line `Act, 1940.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2* * *.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force at once; but Chapter III shall take effect only from such date6`
  line `as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, and`
  line `Chapter IV shall take effect in a particular State only from such date^3`
  line `as the State Government may,`
  line `by like notification, appoint in this behalf :`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that in relation to the State of Jammu and Kashmir*, Chapter III shall take effect only`
  line `from such date^5`
  line `after the commencement of the Drugs and Cosmetics (Amendment) Act, 1972`
  line `(19 of 1972), as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this`
  line behalf.]
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 3 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 19 of 1972, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. 1st April, 1947; see notification No. F. 28(10) (3) 45H(I), dated the 2nd September, 1946, Gazette of India, 1946, Pt. I, p. 1349.`
  line
  line `Ch. IV came into force in the States of Delhi. Ajmer and Coorg on the 1st April, 1947, see ibid., Chs. III and IV came into`
  line `force in the States of H.P., Bilaspur, Kutch, Bhopal, Tripura, Vindhya Pradesh and Manipur on the 1st April, 1953, vide`
  line `notification No. S.R.O. 663, dated the 30th March, 1953, Gazette of India, Pt II, Sec. 3, p. 451.`
  line
  line `Ch. IV came into force in the Union territory of Dadra and Nagar Haveli w.e.f. 1st August, 1968,`
  line `see notification. No. ADM/Law/117(74), dated the 20th July, 1968, Gazette of India, PT. III, Sec. 3, p. 128.`
  line
  line `The Act is extended to Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Sch. I; to Pondicherry by Reg. 7 of 1963, s. 3`
  line `and the Sch. I; to Goa, Daman and Diu by Reg. 11 of 1963, s. 3 and to the whole of the Union territory of Lakshadweep by`
  line `Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and Sch.`
  line
  line `4. Added by Act 19 of 1972, s. 2.`
  line
  line `5. 24th August, 1974, vide notification. No. S.O. 2185, dated the 9th August, 1974, Gazette of India, 1974, Pt. II, Sec. 3 (ii), p. 2331.`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (13994)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=13994&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition`
  line `to, and not in derogation of, the Dangerous Drugs Act, 1930 (2 of 1930), and any other law for`
  line `the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (13995)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=13995&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or`
  line `context, --`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "`
  line `^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drug" includes all medicines intended for`
  line `internal or external use for or in the diagnosis, treatment, mitigation or prevention of`
  line `^3[disease or disorder in human beings or animals, and manufactured] exclusively in`
  line `accordance with the formulae described in, the authoritative books of ^3[Ayurvedic,`
  line `Siddha and Unani Tibb system of medicine], specified in the First Schedule;]`
  line
  line `^4[(aa) "the Board" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to ^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drug, the ^3[Ayurvedic, Siddha`
  line `and Unani Drugs Technical Advisory Board] constituted under section 33C; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other drug or cosmetic, the Drugs Technical Advisory Board`
  line `constituted under section 5;]`
  line
  line ^5[
  line `^6[(aaa)] "cosmetic" means any article intended to be rubbed, poured, sprinkled or`
  line `sprayed on, or introduced into, or otherwise applied to, the human body or any part`
  line `thereof for cleansing, beautifying, promoting attractiveness, or altering the appearance,`
  line `and includes any article intended for use as a component of cosmetic 7`
  line `* * *;]`
  line
  line `^8[(b) "drug" includes--`
  line
  line `^9[(i) all medicines for internal or external use of human beings or animals and all`
  line `substances intended to be used for or in the diagnosis, treatment, mitigation or`
  line `prevention of any disease or disorder in human beings or animals, including`
  line `preparations applied on human body for the purpose of repelling insects like`
  line mosquitoes;]
  line
  line `(ii) such substances (other than food) intended to affect the structure or any`
  line `function of the human body or intended to be used for the destruction of ^10[vermin]`
  line `or insects which cause disease in human beings or animals, as may be specified`
  line `from time to time by the Central Government by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette;]
  line
  line `^11[(iii) all substances intended for use as components of a drug including empty gelatin`
  line `capsules; and`
  line
  line `(iv) such devices intended for internal or external use in the diagnosis, treatment,`
  line `mitigation or prevention of disease or disorder in human beings or animals, as may`
  line `be specified from time to time by the Central Government by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, after consultation with the Board;]`
  line
  line `^12[(c) "Government Analyst" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to ^13[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drug, a Government Analyst`
  line `appointed by the Central Government or a State Government under section 33F; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other drug or cosmetic, a Government Analyst appointed by the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government under section 20;]`
  line
  line `^14* * * * *`
  line
  line `^15[(e) "Inspector" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to ^13[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drug, an Inspector appointed by`
  line `the Central Government or a State Government under section 33G; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other drug or cosmetic, an Inspector appointed by the`
  line `Central Government or a State Government under section 21 ;]`
  line
  line ^16[
  line `^17[(f)] "manufacture" in relation to any drug ^18[or cosmetic] includes any process or part`
  line `of a process for making, altering, ornamenting, finishing, packing, labeling, breaking up or`
  line `otherwise treating or adopting any drug ^18[or cosmetic] with a view to its ^19[sale or distribution] but does`
  line `not include the compounding or dispensing ^20[of any drug, or the packing of any drug or cosmetic,] in the`
  line `ordinary course of retail business; and "to manufacture" shall be construed accordingly;]`
  line
  line `^21[(g)] "to import", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions means to bring into`
  line ^22[India];
  line
  line `^23[ ^21[(h)] "patent or proprietary medicine" means, --`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani Tibb systems of medicine all`
  line `formulations containing only such ingredients mentioned in the formulae described in the`
  line `authoritative books of Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani Tibb systems of medicine specified in`
  line `the First Schedule, but does not include a medicine which is administered by parenteral`
  line `route and also a formulation included in the authoritative books as specified in clause (a);`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other systems of medicine, a drug which is a remedy or`
  line `prescription presented in a form ready for internal or external administration of human`
  line `beings or animals and which is not included in the edition of the Indian Pharmacopoeia`
  line `for the time being or any other Pharmacopoeia authorised in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government after consultation with the Drugs Technical Adivisory Board constituted`
  line `under section 5;]`
  line
  line `^24[ ^21[(i)] "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.]`
  line
  line `^25* * * * *`
