  line
  line `25. Cl. (f) omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (13996)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Construction of references to any law not in force or any functionary not in existence in the State of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=13996&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Construction of references to any law not in force or any functionary not in existence in`
  line `the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.--Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force, or any`
  line `functionary not in existence, in the State of Jammu and Kashmir*, shall, in relation to that State, be`
  line `construed as a reference to the corresponding law in force, or to the corresponding functionary in`
  line `existence, in that State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 1972, s. 4.`
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (13997)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Presumption as to poisonous substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. Act 13 of 1964, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=13997&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Any substance specified as poisonous by`
  line `rule made under Chapter II or Chapter IV ^1[or Chapter IVA] shall be deemed to be a poisonous`
  line `substance for the purposes of Chapter III or Chapter IV ^1[or Chapter IVA], as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (13998)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `The Drugs Technical Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=13998&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as may`
  line `be, constitute a Board (to be called the Drugs Technical Advisory Board) to advise the Central`
  line `Government and the State Governments on technical matters arising out of the administration of`
  line `this Act and to carry out the other functions assigned to it by this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the Director General of Health Services, ex officio, who shall be the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Drugs Controller, India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Director of the Central Drugs Laboratory, Calcutta, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Director of the Central Research Institute, Kasauli, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) the Director of the Indian Veterinary Research Institute, Izatnagar, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) the President of the Medical Council of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vii) the President of the Pharmacy Council of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(viii) the Director of the Central Drug Research Institute, Lucknow, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ix) two persons to be nominated by the Central Government from among persons`
  line `who are in charge of drugs control in the States;`
  line
  line `(x) one person, to be elected by the Executive Committee of the Pharmacy Council of`
  line `India, from among teachers in pharmacy or pharmaceutical chemistry or pharmacognosy on`
  line `the staff of an Indian university or a college affiliated thereto;`
  line
  line `(xi) one person, to be elected by the Executive Committee of the Medical Council of India, from`
  line `among teachers in medicine or therapeutics on the staff of an Indian university or a college affiliated`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(xii) one person to be nominated by the Central Government from the pharmaceutical`
  line industry;
  line
  line `(xiii) one pharmacologist to be elected by the Governing Body of the Indian Council of Medical`
  line Research;
  line
  line `(xiv) one person to be elected by the Central Council of the Indian Medical`
  line Association;
  line
  line `(xv) one person to be elected by the Council of the Indian Pharmaceutical`
  line Association;
  line
  line `(xvi) two persons holding the appointment of Government Analyst under this Act, to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) The nominated and elected members of the Board shall hold office for three years, but shall be`
  line `eligible for re-nomination and re-election :`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the person nominated or elected, as the case may be, under clause (ix) or`
  line `clause (x) or clause (xi) or clause (xvi) of sub-section (2) shall hold office for so long as he holds`
  line `the appointment of the office by virtue of which he was nominated or elected to the Board.]`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may, subject to the previous approval of the Central Government, make bye -`
  line `laws fixing a quorum and regulating its own procedure and the conduct of all business to be`
  line `transacted by it.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board may constitute sub-committees and may appoint to such sub-committees for`
  line `such periods, not exceeding three years, as it may decide , or temporarily for the consideration`
  line `of particular matters, persons who are not members of the Board.`
  line
  line `(6) The functions of the Board may be exercised notwithstanding any vacancy therein.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government shall appoint a person to be Secretary of the Board and shall`
  line `provide the Board with such clerical and other staff as the Central Government considers`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 4, for the proviso (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (13999)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `The Central Drugs Laboratory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=13999&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as may`
  line `be, establish a Central Drugs Laboratory under the control of a Director to be appointed by`
  line `the Central Government, to carry out the functions entrusted to it by this Act or any rules`
  line `made under this Chapter :`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the Central Government so prescribes, the functions of th e Central Drugs`
  line `Laboratory in respect of any drug or class of drugs ^1[or cosmetic or class of cosmetics] shall be`
  line `carried out at the Central Research Institute, Kasauli, or at any other prescribed Laboratory and`
  line `the functions of the Director of the Central Drugs Laboratory in respect of such drug or class of`
  line `drugs ^1[or such cosmetic or class of cosmetics] shall be exercised by the Director of that`
  line `Institute or of that other Laboratory, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, after consultation with the Board, make rules`
  line prescribing
  line
  line `(a) the functions of the Central Drugs Laboratory;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure for the submission to the said Laboratory ^3[under Chapter IV or`
  line `Chapter IVA] of samples of drugs ^1[or cosmetics] for analysis or test, the forms of the`
  line `Laboratorys reports thereon and the fees payable in respect of such reports;`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as may be necessary or expedient to enable the said Laboratory to carry`
  line `out its functions;`
  line
  line `(f) the matters necessary to be prescribed for the purposes of the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 5 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Cls. (b) and (c) omitted by Act 11 of 1955, s. 4.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 5, for under Chapter IV (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (14000)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `The Drugs Consultative Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch., for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=14000&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may constitute an`
  line `advisory committee to be called "the Drugs Consultative Committee" to advise the Central`
  line `Government, the State Governments and the Drugs Technical Advisory Board on any matter`
  line `tending to secure uniformity throughout ^1[India] in the administration of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Drugs Consultative Committee shall consist of two representatives of the Central`
  line `Government to be nominated by that Government and one representative of each State`
  line `Government to be nominated by the State Government concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) The Drugs Consultative Committee shall meet when required to do so by the Central Government`
  line `and shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (27610)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 9
  title `Sections 5 and 7 not to apply to Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drugs`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27610&sectionno=7A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Sections 5 and 7 not to apply to Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drugs.--Nothing contained`
  line `in sections 5 and 7 shall apply to ^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drugs.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (27611)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Standards of quality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27611&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Standards of quality.--^2[(1) For the purposes of this Chapter, the expression "standard quality"`
  line means--
  line
  line `(a) in relation to a drug, that the drug complies with the standard set out in ^3[the Second`
  line `Schedule], and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to a cosmetic, that the cosmetic complies with such standard as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government, after consultation with the Board and after giving by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette not less than three months' notice of its intention so to do, may by a like`
  line `notification add to or otherwise amend ^3[the Second Schedule], for the purposes of this Chapter,`
  line `and thereupon ^3[the Second Schedule] shall be deemed to be amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for the heading under Chapter III (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 7, for "the Schedule" (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (27612)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Misbranded drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 5, for section 9 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27612&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Misbranded drugs.--For the purposes of this Chapter, a drug shall be deemed to be`
  line misbranded--
  line
  line `(a) if it is so coloured, coated, powdered or polished that damage is concealed or if it is made to`
  line `appear of better or greater therapeutic value than it really is; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is not labelled in the prescribed manner; or`
  line
  line `(c) if its label or container or anything accompanying the drug bears any statement, design`
  line `or device which makes any false claim for the drug or which is false or misleading in any`
  line particular.]
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (27613)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 12
  title `Adulterated drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sections 9A and 9B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27613&sectionno=9A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Adulterated drugs.-- For the purposes of this Chapter, a drug shall be deemed to be`
  line adulterated,--
  line
  line `(a) if it consists, in whole or in part, of any filthy, putrid or decomposed substance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it has been prepared, packed or stored under insanitary conditions whereby it may`
  line `have been contaminated with filth or whereby it may have been rendered injurious to health;`
  line
  line `(c) if its container is composed in whole or in part, of any poisonous or deleterious`
  line `substance which may render the contents injurious to hea lth; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it bears or contains, for purposes of colouring only, a colour other than one which is`
  line `prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it contains any harmful or toxic substance which may render it injurious to`
  line `health; or`
  line
  line `(f) if any substance has been mixed therewith so as to reduce its quality or strength.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (27614)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 13
  title `Spurious drugs`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sections 9A and 9B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27614&sectionno=9B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[9B. Spurious drugs.--For the purposes of this Chapter, a drug shall be deemed to be`
  line spurious--
  line
  line `(a) if it is imported under a name which belongs to another drug; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is an imitation of, or is a substitute for, another drug or resembles another drug in`
  line `a manner likely to deceive or bears upon it or upon its label or container the name of another`
  line `drug unless it is plainly and conspicuously marked so as to reveal its true character and its`
  line `lack of identity with such other drug; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the label or container bears the name of an individual or company purporting to`
  line `be the manufacturer of the drug, which individual or company is fictitious or does not`
  line `exist; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it has been substituted wholly or in part by another drug or substance; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it purports to be the product of a manufacturer of whom it is not truly a product.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_c:
  sectionId (27615)
  sectionNo 9C
  orderNo 14
  title `Misbranded cosmetics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sections 9A and 9B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27615&sectionno=9C&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[9C. Misbranded cosmetics.--For the purposes of this Chapter, a cosmetic shall be deemed to be`
  line misbranded--
  line
  line `(a) if it contains a colour which is not prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is not labelled in the prescribed manner; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the label or container or anything accompanying the cosmetic bears any`
  line `statement which is false or misleading in any particular.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_d:
  sectionId (27616)
  sectionNo 9D
  orderNo 15
  title `Spurious cosmetics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sections 9A and 9B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27616&sectionno=9D&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_9_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[9D. Spurious cosmetics.--For the purposes of this Chapter, a cosmetic shall be deemed to be`
  line spurious,--
  line
  line `(a) if it is imported under a name which belongs to another cosmetic; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is an imitation of, or is a substitute for, another cosmetic or resembles another`
  line `cosmetic in a manner likely to deceive or bears upon it or upon its label or container the`
  line `name of another cosmetic, unless it is plainly and conspicuously marked so as to reveal its`
  line `true character and its lack of identity with such other cosmetic; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the label ,`
  line `or container bears the name of an individual or a company purporting to`
  line `be the manufacturer of the cosmetic which individual or company is fictitious or does not`
  line `exist; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it purports to be product of a manufacture of whom it is not truly a product.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (27617)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 16
  title `Prohibition of import of certain drugs or cosmetics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27617&sectionno=10&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `From such date^1`
  line `as may be fixed`
  line `by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette in this behalf, no person shall`
  line import--
  line
  line `(a) any drug ^2[or cosmetic] which is not of standard quality;`
  line
  line `^3[(b) any misbranded drug ^4[or misbranded or spurious cosmetics];]`
  line
  line `^5[(bb) any ^6[adulterated or spurious;] drug;]`
  line
  line `(c) any drug ^2[or cosmetic] for the import of which a licence is prescribed, otherwise`
  line `than under, in accordance with, such licence;`
  line
  line `^7[(d) any patent or proprietary medicine, unless there is displayed in the prescribed`
  line `manner on the label or container thereof ^8[the true formula or list of active ingredients contained in it together with the quantities thereof];]`
  line
  line `(e) any drug which by means of any statement, design or device accompanying it or`
  line `by any other means, purports or claims to cure or mitigate any such disease or ailment,`
  line `or to have any such other effect, as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `^2[(ee) any cosmetic containing any ingredient which may render it unsafe or`
  line `harmful for use under the directions indicated or recommended;]`
  line
  line `(f) any drug ^2[or cosmetic] the import of which is prohibited by rule made`
  line `under this Chapter :`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to the import, subject to prescribed con -`
  line `ditions, of small quantities of any drug for the purpose of examination, test or ana lysis or for`
  line `personal use :`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, after consultation with the Board, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, permit, subject to any conditions specified in the`
  line `notification, the import of any drug or class of drugs not being of standard quality.`
  line
  line `^9* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st April, 1947, for cls. (a), (b), (c), (e) and (f) and 1st April, 1949, for cl. (d), see notification No. 18-12-46-D-I, dated the 11th`
  line `February, 1947, Gazette of India, 1947, Pt. I, p 189 as amended by notification No. F-1-2/48-D(I), dated the 29th September,`
  line `1948, 1st April, 1953, for the State of H.P., Bilaspur, Kutch, Bhopal, Tripura, Vindhya Pradesh and Manipur vide notification`
  line `No. S.R.O. 666, dated the 30th March, 1953, Gazette of India, 1953, Pt. II, Sec. 3, p. 451.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 8 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 7, for "or misbranded cosmetic" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 9 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `6. Subs, by Act 68 of 1982; s. 7, for "adulterated" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 5, for clause (d).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 7, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `9. The Explanation omitted by Act 68 of 1982, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (27618)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of Central Government to prohibit import of drugs and cosmetics in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27618&sectionno=10A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Power of Central Government to prohibit import of drugs and cosmetics in`
  line `public interest.--Without prejudice to any other provision contained in this Chapter, if the`
  line `Central Government is satisfied that the use of any drug or cosmetic is likely to involve any`
  line `risk to human beings or animals or that any drug does not have the therapeutic value claimed`
  line `for it or contains ingredients and in such quantity for which there is no therapeutic justification`
  line `and that in the public interest it is necessary or expedient so to do then, that Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, prohibit the import of such drug or cosmetic.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (27619)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 18
  title `Application of law relating to sea customs and powers of Customs officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27619&sectionno=11&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `law for the time being in force relating to sea customs and to goods, the import of which is prohibited`
  line `by section 18 of the Sea Customs Act, 1878 ^1 (18 of 1878) shall, subject to the provisions`
  line `of section 13 of this Act, apply in respect of drugs ^2[and cosmetics] the import of which is`
  line `prohibited under this Chapter and officers of Customs and officers empowered under that Act`
  line `to perform the duties imposed thereby on a ^3[Commissioner of Custom and other officers of Customs, shall have the same powers in respect of such drugs ^4[and cosmetics] as they have for the time`
  line `being in respect of such goods as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the ^6[Commissioner of`
  line `Customs] or any officer of the Government authorised by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf, may detain any imported package which he suspects to contain any drug ^4[or`
  line `cosmetic] the import of which is prohibited under this Chapter and shall forthwith report`
  line `such detention to the Drugs Controller, India and, if necessary, forward the p ackage or`
  line `sample of any suspected drug ^4[or cosmetic] found therein to the Central Drugs Laboratory.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Now see the Customs Act, 1962.`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 9 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 83, for "Customs Collector".`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 9 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `5 Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 6, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `6 Subs. by Act 22 of 1995, s. 83, for "Customs Collector".`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (27620)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27620&sectionno=12&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `^1[after consultation with or on the recommendation of the Board] and after previous publication`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter :`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that consultation with the Board may be dispensed with if the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that circumstances have arisen which render it necessary to make`
  line `rules without such consultation, but in such a case the Board shall be consulted within six`
  line `months of the making of the rules and the Central Government shall take into consideration`
  line `any suggestions which the Board may make in relation to the amendment of the said rules.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line
  line `(a) specify the drugs or classes of drugs ^3[or cosmetics or classes of cosmetics] for the`
  line `import of which a licence is required, ^4[and prescribed the form and conditions of such`
  line `licences, the authority empowered to issue the same, the fees payable therefor and provide`
  line `for the cancellation, or suspension of such licence in any case where any provision of this`
  line `Chapter or the rules made thereunder is contravened or any of the conditions subject to`
  line `which the licence is issued is not complied with] ;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the methods of test or analysis to be employed in determining whether a drug`
  line `^3[or cosmetic] is of standard quality ;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe, in respect of biological and organometallic compounds, the units or methods of`
  line standardisation;
  line
  line `^5[(cc) prescribe under clause (d) of ^6[section 9A] the colour or colours which a drug`
  line `may bear or contain for purposes of colouring;]`
  line
  line `(d) specify the diseases or ailments which an imported drug may not purport or claim`
  line `^7[to prevent, cure or mitigate] and such other effects which such drug may not purport or`
  line `claim to have;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribe the conditions subject to which small quantities of drugs, the import of`
  line `which is otherwise prohibited under this Chapter, may be imported for the purpose of`
  line `examination, test or analysis or for personal use;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribe the places at which drugs ^3[or cosmetics] may be imported, and prohibited their`
  line `import at any other place;`
  line
  line `(g) require the date of manufacture and the date of expiry of potency to be clearly and`
  line `truely stated on the label or container of any specified imported drug or class of such drug,`
  line `and prohibit the import of the said drug or class of drug after the expiry of a specified period`
  line `from the date of manufacture;`
  line
  line `(h) regulate the submission by importers, and the securing, of samples of drugs`
  line `^8[or cosmetics] for examination, test or analysis by the Central Drugs Laboratory, and`
  line `prescribed the fees, if any, payable for such examination, test or analysis;`
  line
  line `(i) prescribe the evidence to be supplied, whether by accompanying documents or`
  line `otherwise, of the quality of drugs ^66[or cosmetics] sought to be imported, the procedure of`
  line `officers of Customs in dealing with such evidence, and the manner of storage at places of`
  line `import of drugs ^8[or cosmetics] detained pending admission;`
  line
  line `(j) provide for the exemption, conditionally or otherwise, from all or any of the provisions`
  line `of this Chapter and the rules made thereunder of drugs ^8[or cosmetics] imported for the`
  line `purpose only of transport through, and export from, ^9[India];`
  line
  line `(k) prescribe the conditions to be observed in the packing in bottles, packages or other`
  line `containers, of imported drugs ^8[or cosmetics] ^10[including the use of packing material which comes`
  line `into direct contact with the drugs];`
  line
  line `(l) regulate the mode of labelling drugs ^8[or cosmetics] imported for sale in packages, and`
  line `prescribe the matters which shall or shall not be included in such labels;`
  line
  line `(m) prescribe the maximum proportion of any poisonous substance which may be added`
  line `to or contained in any imported drug, prohibit the import of any drug in which that proportion`
  line `is exceeded, and specify substances which shall be deemed to be poisonous for the purposes`
  line `of this Chapter and the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(n) require that the accepted scientific name of any specified drug shall be displayed in the`
  line `prescribed manner on the label or wrapper of any imported, patent or proprietary medicine`
  line `containing such drug ;`
  line
  line `(o) provide for the exemption, conditionally or otherwise, from all or any of the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter or the rules made thereunder of any specified drug or class of drugs ^8[or cosmetics or`
  line `class of cosmetics].`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 9, for "after consultation with the Board" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 7.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 10 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 9, for "section 9B" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 7 for "to cure or mitigate".`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 10 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., for "the States".`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (27621)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 20
  title Offences
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 13 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27621&sectionno=13&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[13. Offenees.-- (1) Whoever himself or by any other person on his behalf imports,--`
  line
  line `(a) any drug deemed to be adulterated under section 9A or deemed to be a spurious drug`
  line `under section 9B or any spurious cosmetic referred to in section 9D or any cosmetic of the`
  line `nature referred to in clause (ee) of section 10 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years and a fine which may extend to five thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) any drug or cosmetic other than a drug or cosmetic referred to in clause (a), the`
  line `import of which is prohibited under section 10, or any rule made under this Chapter, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(c) any drug or cosmetic in contravention of the provisions of any notification issued under`
  line `section 10A, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever having been convicted of an offence--`
  line
  line `(a) under clause (a) or clause (c) of sub-section (1), is again convicted of an offence`
  line `under that clause, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `five years, or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) under clause (b) of sub-section (1), is again convicted of an offence under that`
  line `clause, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year,`
  line `or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) The punishment provided by this section shall be in addition to any penalty to which`
  line `the offender may be liable under the provisions of section 11.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (27622)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 21
  title Confiscation
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 11 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27622&sectionno=14&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where any offence punishable under section 13 has been committed, the`
  line `consignment of the drugs ^1[or cosmetics] in respect of which the offence has been committed shall be`
  line `liable to confiscation.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (27623)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 22
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27623&sectionno=15&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No Court inferior to that ^1[of a Metropolitan Magistrate or of a Judicial Magistrate`
  line `of the first class] shall try an offence punishable under section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (27624)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 23
  title `Standards of quality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27624&sectionno=16&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Drugs ^1[and Cosmetics]`
  line `Act, 1940.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2* * *.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force at once; but Chapter III shall take effect only from such date^3`
  line `as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, and`
  line `Chapter IV shall take effect in a particular State only from such date^3`
  line `as the State Government may,`
  line `by like notification, appoint in this behalf :`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that in relation to the State of Jammu and Kashmir, Chapter III shall take effect only`
  line `from such date^5`
  line `after the commencement of the Drugs and Cosmetics (Amendment) Act, 1972`
  line `(19 of 1972), as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this`
  line behalf.]
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 3 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 19 of 1972, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. 1st April, 1947; see notification No. F. 28(10) (3) 45H(I), dated the 2nd September, 1946, Gazette of India, 1946, Pt. I, p. 1349.`
  line
  line `Ch. IV came into force in the States of Delhi. Ajmer and Coorg on the 1st April, 1947, see ibid., Chs. III and IV came into`
  line `force in the States of H.P., Bilaspur, Kutch, Bhopal, Tripura, Vindhya Pradesh and Manipur on the 1st April, 1953, vide`
  line `notification No. S.R.O. 663, dated the 30th March, 1953, Gazette of India, Pt II, Sec. 3, p. 451.`
  line
  line `Ch. IV came into force in the Union territory of Dadra and Nagar Haveli w.e.f. 1st August, 1968,`
  line `see notification. No. ADM/Law/117(74), dated the 20th July, 1968, Gazette of India, PT. III, Sec. 3, p. 128.`
  line
  line `The Act is extended to Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Sch. I; to Pondicherry by Reg. 7 of 1963, s. 3`
  line `and the Sch. I; to Goa, Daman and Diu by Reg. 11 of 1963, s. 3 and to the whole of the Union territory of Lakshadweep by`
  line `Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and Sch.`
  line
  line `4. Added by Act 19 of 1972, s. 2.`
  line
  line `5. 24th August, 1974, vide notification. No. S.O. 2185, dated the 9th August, 1974, Gazette of India, 1974, Pt. II, Sec. 3 (ii), p. 2331.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (27625)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 24
  title `Misbranded drugs`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 13, for sections 17, 17A and 17B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27625&sectionno=17&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Misbranded drugs.-- For the purposes of this Chapter, a drug shall be deemed to be`
  line misbranded,--
  line
  line `(a) if it is so coloured, coated, powdered or polished that damage is concealed or if it`
  line `is made to appear of better or greater therapeutic value than it really is; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is not labelled in the prescribed manner; or`
  line
  line `(c) if its label or container or anything accompanying the drug bears any statement,`
  line `design or device which makes any false claim for the drug or which is false or misleading in`
  line `any particular.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (27626)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 25
  title `Adulterated drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 13, for sections 17, 17A and 17B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27626&sectionno=17A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Adulterated drugs.--For the purposes of this Chapter, a drug shall be deemed to be`
  line adulterated,--
  line
  line `(a) if it consists in whole or in part, of any filthy, putrid or decomposed substance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it has been prepared, packed or stored under insanitary conditions whereby it`
  line `may have been contaminated with filth or whereby it may have been rendered injurious to`
  line `health; or`
  line
  line `(c) if its container is composed, in whole or in part, of any poisonous or deleterious`
  line `substance which may render the contents injurious to health; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it bears or contains, for purposes of colouring only, a colour other than one which is`
  line `prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it contains any harmful or toxic substance which may render it injurious to`
  line `health; or`
  line
  line `(f) if any substance has been mixed therewith so as to reduce its quality or strength.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_b:
  sectionId (27627)
  sectionNo 17B
  orderNo 26
  title `Spurious drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 13, for sections 17, 17A and 17B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27627&sectionno=17B&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_17_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[17B. Spurious drugs.--For the purposes of this Chapter, a drug shall be deemed to be`
  line spurious,--
  line
  line `(a) if it is manufactured under a name which belongs to another drug; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is an imitation of, or is a substitute for, another drug or resembles another drug`
  line `in a manner likely to deceive or bears upon it or upon its label or container the name of`
  line `another drug unless it is plainly and conspicuously marked so as to reveal its true character`
  line `and its lack of identity with such other drug; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the label or container bears the name of an individual or company purporting to be the`
  line `manufacturer of the drug, which individual or company is fictitious or does not exist; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it has been substituted wholly or in part by another drug or substance; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it purports to be the product of a manufacturer of whom it is not truly a product.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_c:
  sectionId (27628)
  sectionNo 17C
  orderNo 27
  title `Misbranded cosmetics`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 13, for sections 17, 17A and 17B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27628&sectionno=17C&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_17_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[17C. Misbranded cosmetics.--For the purposes of this Chapter, a cosmetic shall be deemed to be`
  line misbranded,--
  line
  line `(a) if it contains a colour which is not prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is not labelled in the prescribed manner; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the label or container or anything accompanying the cosmetic bears any statement`
  line `which is false or misleading in any particular.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_d:
  sectionId (27629)
  sectionNo 17D
  orderNo 28
  title `Spurious cosmetics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 13, for sections 17, 17A and 17B (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27629&sectionno=17D&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_17_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[17D. Spurious cosmetics.--For the purposes of this Chapter, a cosmetic shall be deemed to be`
  line spurious,--
  line
  line `(a) if it is manufactured under a name which belongs to another cosmetic; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is an imitation of, or a substitute for, another cosmetic or resembles another`
  line `cosmetic in a manner likely to deceive or bears upon it or upon its label or container the`
  line `name of another cosmetic unless it is plainly and conspicuously marked so as to re veal its`
  line `true character and its lack of identity with such other cosmetic; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the label or container bears the name of an individual or a company purporting to`
  line `be the manufacturer of the cosmetic which individual or company is fictitious or does not`
  line `exist; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it purports to be the product of a manufacturer of whom it is not truly a product.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_e:
  sectionId (27630)
  sectionNo 17E
  orderNo 29
  title `Adulterated cosmetics`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27630&sectionno=17E&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_17_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[17E. Adulterated cosmetics. -- For the purposes of this Chapter, a cosmetic shall be deemed to be`
  line adulterated,--
  line
  line `(a) if it consists in whole or in part, of any filthy, putrid or decomposed substance; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it has been prepared, packed or stored under insanitary conditions whereby it may have`
  line `been contaminated with filth or whereby it may have been rendered injurious to health; or`
  line
  line `(c) if its container is composed, in whole or in part, of any poisonous or deleterious substance`
  line `which may render the contents injurious to health; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it bears or contains, for purposes of colouring only, a colour other than one which is`
  line `prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it contains any harmful or toxic substance which may render it injurious to health; or`
  line
  line `(f) if any substance has been mixed therewith so as to reduce its quality or strength.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (27631)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 30
  title `Prohibition of manufacture and sale of certain drugs and cosmetics`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27631&sectionno=18&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `From such ^1date as`
  line `may be fixed by the State Government by notification in the Official Gazette in this behalf, no person`
  line `shall himself or by any other person on his behalf--`
  line
  line `(a) ^2[manufacture for sale or for distribution, or sell, or stock or exhibit or offer for sale,] or`
  line distribute
  line
  line `^3[(i) any drug which is not of a standard quality, or is misbranded, adulterated or spurious;`
  line
  line `^4[(ii) any cosmetic which is not of a standard quality or is misbranded, adulterated or`
  line spurious;]]
  line
  line `^5[(iii) any patent or proprietary medicine, unless there is displayed in the prescribed`
  line `manner on the label or container thereof ^2[the true formula or list of active ingredients`
  line `contained in it together with the quantities thereof];]`
  line
  line `(iv) any drug which by means of any statement design or device accompanying it or`
  line `by any other means, purports or claims ^6[to prevent, cure or mitigate] any such disease or`
  line `ailment, or to have any such other effect as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `^7[(v) any cosmetic containing any ingredient which may render it unsafe or harmful for use`
  line `under the directions indicated or recommended;`
  line
  line `(vi) any drug or cosmetic in contravention of any of the provisions of this Chapter or any`
  line `rule made thereunder;]`
  line
  line `(b) ^2[sell or stock or exhibit or offer for sale,] or distribute any drug ^8[or cosmetic] which has been`
  line `imported or manufacutred in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or any rule made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(c) ^2[manufacture for sale or for distribution, or sell, or stock or exhibit or offer for sale,]`
  line `or distribute any drug ^8[or cosmetic], except under, and in accordance with the conditions`
  line `of, a licence issued for such purpose under this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to the manufacture, subject to prescribed`
  line `conditions, of small quantities of any drug for the purpose of examination, test or analysis :`
  line
  line `Provided further that the ^9[Central Government] may, after consultation with the Board, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, permit, subject to any conditions specified in the notifica tion,`
  line `the ^10[manufacture for sale or for distribution, sale, stocking or exhibiting or offering for sale] or`
  line `distribution of any drug or class of drugs not being of standard quality.`
  line
  line `^11* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st April, 1947 for sub-clauses (i), (ii), (iv) and (v) of cl. (a) and cls. (b) and (c); 1st April, 1949 for sub-clause (iii) of`
  line `cl. (a) in so far as it takes effect in Delhi, Ajmer and Coorg, see Notifn. No. 18-12-46-D, II, dated 11th February, 1947, Gazette of`
  line `India, 1947, Pt. I, p. 189, as amended by notifn. No. F. 1-2/48-D (ii), dated 29th September, 1948; 1st April, 1953 for the States of`
  line `H. P., Bilaspur, Kutch, Bhopal, Tripura, Vindhya Pradesh and Manipur, vide notifn. No. S.R.O. 664, dated the 30th March, 1953,`
  line `Gazette of India, 1953, Pt. II, Sec. 3, p. 451`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982. s. 14, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid, for cls. (i), (ii) and (iia) (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 3, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f.10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 9, for sub-clause (iii).`
  line
  line `6. Subs by s. 9, ibid., for to cure or mitigate.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 14, for sub-clause (v) (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 9, for "State Government".`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 14, for "manufacture for sale, sale" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `11. The Explanation omitted by Act 68 of 1982, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (27635)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 31
  title `Disclosure of the name of the manufacturer, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27635&sectionno=18A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Disclosure of the name of the manufacturer, etc.--Every person, not being the`
  line `manufacturer of a drug or cosmetic or his agent for the distribution thereof, shall, if so required, disclose`
  line `to the Inspector the name, address and other particulars of the person from whom he acquired the drug or`
  line cosmetic.]
obj_root_law_sections_18_b:
  sectionId (27636)
  sectionNo 18B
  orderNo 32
  title `Maintenance of records and furnishing of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27636&sectionno=18B&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_18_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[18B. Maintenance of records and furnishing of information.--Every person holding a`
  line `licence under clause (c) of section 18 shall keep and maintain such records, registers and other`
  line `documents as may be prescribed and shall furnish to any officer or authority exercising any`
  line `power or discharging any function under this Act such information as is required by such officer`
  line `or authority for carrying out the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (27637)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 33
  title Pleas.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27637&sectionno=19&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as hereinafter provided in this section, it shall be no defence in a prosecution under this Chapter to prove merely that the accused was ignorant of the nature, sub stance`
  line `or quality of the drug ^1[or cosmetic] in respect of which the offence has been committed or of the`
  line `circumstances of its manufacture or import, or that a purchaser, having bought only for the purpose`
  line `of test or analysis, has not been prejudiced by the sale.`
  line
  line `(2) ^2[For the purposes of section 18 a drug shall not be deemed to be misbranded or`
  line `^3[adulterated or spurious] or to be below standard quality nor shall a cosmetic be deemed to be`
  line `misbranded or to be below standard quality] only by reason of the fact that--`
  line
  line `(a) there has been added thereto some innocuous substance or ingredient because the`
  line `same is required for the manufacture or preparation of the drug ^1[or cosmetic] as an article`
  line `of commerce in a state fit for carriage or consumption, and not to increase the bulk, weight`
  line `or measure of the drug ^1[or cosmetic] or to conceal its inferior quality or other defects; or`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) in the process of manufacture, preparation or conveyance some extraneous substance`
  line `has unavoidably become intermixed with it: provided that this clause shall not apply in`
  line `relation to any sale or distribution of the drug ^1`
  line `[or cosmetic] occurring after the vendor or`
  line `distributor became aware of such intermixture.`
  line
  line `^5[(3) A person, not being the manufacturer of a drug or cosmetic or his agent for the distribution`
  line `thereof, shall not be liable for a contravention of section 18 if he proves--`
  line
  line `(a) that he acquired the drug or cosmetic from a duly licensed manufacturer, distributor or dealer`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `(b) that he did not know and could not, with reasonable diligence, have ascertained that`
  line `the drug or cosmetic in any way contravened the provisions of that section; and`
  line
  line `(c) that the drug or cosmetic, while in his possession, was properly stored a nd`
  line `remained in the same state as when he acquired it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 15 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 15, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 16, for "adulterated" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Cl. (aa) ins. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 10, omitted by Act 13 of 1964, s. 15 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 15, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (27638)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 34
  title `Government Analysts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27638&sectionno=20&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Government Analysts.--(1) The State Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint such persons as it thinks fit, having the prescribed qualifications, to be`
  line `Government Analysts for such areas in the State and in respect of such drugs or ^2[classes of`
  line `drugs or such cosmetics or classes of cosmetics] as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may also, by notification in the Official Gaz ette, appoint such`
  line `persons as it thinks fit, having the prescribed qualifications, to be Government Analysts in`
  line `respect of such drugs or ^2[classes of drugs or such cosmetics or classes of cosmetics] as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), neither the`
  line `Central Government nor a State Government shall appoint as a Government Analyst any`
  line `official not serving under it without the previous consent of the Government und er which he`
  line `is serving.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) No person who has any financial interest in the import, manufacture or sale of drugs`
  line `or cosmetics shall be appointed to be a Government Analyst under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of`
  line `this section.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by Act 35 of 1960, s. 4, for the original sections 20 and 21 (w.e.f. 16-3-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 16, for "class of drugs" (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `36. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (27639)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 35
  title Inspectors
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27639&sectionno=21&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Inspectors.--(1) The Central Government or a State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint such persons as it thinks fit, having the`
  line `prescribed qualifications, to be Inspectors for such areas as may be assigned to them by the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers which may be exercised by an Inspector and the duties which may be`
  line `performed by him, the drugs or ^2[classes of drugs or cosmetics or classes of cosmetics] in`
  line `relation to which and the conditions, limitations or restrictions subject to which, such powers`
  line `and duties may be exercised or performed shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) No person who has any financial interest ^3[in the import, manufacture or sale of drugs or`
  line `cosmetics] shall be appointed to be an Inspector under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Inspector shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and shall be officially subordinate to such`
  line authority
  line `^4[having the prescribed qualifications, as the Government appointing him may`
  line `specify in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by Act 35 of 1960, s. 4, for the original sections 20 and 21 (w.e.f. 16-3-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 17, for "class of drugs" (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "in the manufacture, import or sale of drugs" (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (27640)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 36
  title `Powers of Inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27640&sectionno=22&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Powers of Inspectors.--(1) Subject to the provisions of section 23 and of any rules`
  line `made by the Central Government in this behalf, an Inspector may, within the local limits of`
  line `the area for which he is appointed,--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) inspect,--`
  line
  line `(i) any premises wherein any drug or cosmetic is being manufactured and the`
  line `means employed for standardising and testing the drug or cosmetic;`
  line
  line `(ii) any premises wherein any drug or cosmetic is being sold, or stocked or`
  line `exhibited or offered for sale, or distributed;`
  line
  line `(b) take samples of any drug or cosmetic, --`
  line
  line `(i) which is being manufactured or being sold or is stocked or exhibited or offered for sale,`
  line `or is being distributed;`
  line
  line `(ii) from any person who is in the course of conveying, delivering or preparing to`
  line `deliver such drug or cosmetic to a purchaser or a consignee;`
  line
  line `(c) at all reasonable times, with such assistance, if any, as he considers`
  line necessary,--
  line
  line `(i) search any person, who, he has reason to believe, has secreted about his person,`
  line `any drug or cosmetic in respect of which an offence under this Chapter has been, or is`
  line `being, committed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) enter and search any place in which he has reason to believe that an offence`
  line `under this Chapter has been, or is being, committed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) stop and search any vehicle, vessel or other conveyance which, he has reason`
  line `to believe, is being used for carrying any drug or cosmetic in respect of which an`
  line `offence under this Chapter has been, or is being, committed,`
  line
  line `and order in writing the person in possession of the drug or cosmetic in respect of which the`
  line `offence has been, or is being, committed, not to dispose of any stock of such dru g or cosmetic`
  line `for a specified period not exceeding twenty days, or, unless the alleged offence is such that`
  line `the defect may be removed by the possessor of the drug or cosmetic, seize the stock of such`
  line `drug or cosmetic and any substance or article by means of which the offence has been, or is`
  line `being, committed or which may be employed for the commission of such offence;]`
  line
  line `^3[(cc) examine any record, register, document or any other material object found ^4[with`
  line `any person, or in any place, vehicle, vessel or other conveyance referred to in clause (c)],`
  line `and seize the same if he has reason to believe that it may furnish evidence of the`
  line `commission of an offence punishable under this Act or the rules made thereunder;]`
  line
  line `^5[(cca) require any person to produce any record, register, or other document relating`
  line `to the manufacture for sale or for distribution, stocking, exhibition for sale, offer for sale`
  line `or distribution of any drug or cosmetic in respect of which he has reason to believe that an`
  line `offence under this Chapter has been, or is being, committed;]`
  line
  line `(d) exercise such other powers as may be necessary for carrying out the purposes of`
  line `this Chapter or any rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of ^6[the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)] shall, so far as`
  line `may be, apply to any search or seizure under this Chapter as they apply to any search or`
  line `seizure made under the authority of a warrant issued under ^7[section 94] of the said Code.`
  line
  line `^5[(2A) Every record, register or other document seized under clause (cc) or produced under`
  line `clause (cca) shall be returned to the person, from whom they were seized or who produce the`
  line
  line `same, within a period of twenty days of the date of such seizure or production, as the case may`
  line `be, after copies thereof or extracts therefrom certified by that person, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, have been taken.]`
  line
  line `(3) If any person wilfully obstructs an Inspector in the exercise of the powers conferred`
  line `upon him by or under this Chapter ^8[or refuses to produce any record, register or other`
  line `document when so required under clause (cca) of sub-section (1),] he shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 11, for s. 22.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 19, for cls. (a), (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 35 of 1960, s. 5 (w.e.f. 16-3-1961).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 19, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "section 98" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (27641)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 37
  title `Procedure of Inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27641&sectionno=23&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an Inspector takes any sample of a drug ^1[or`
  line `cosmetic] under this Chapter, he shall tender the fair price thereof and may require a written`
  line `acknowledgment therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the price tendered under sub-section (1) is refused, or where the Inspector seizes`
  line `the stock of any drug ^1[or cosmetic] under clause (c) of section 22, he shall tender a receipt`
  line `therefor in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an Inspector takes a sample of a drug ^1[or cosmetic] for the purpose of test or`
  line `analysis, he shall intimate such purpose in writing in the prescribed form to the person from`
  line `whom he takes it and, in the presence of such person unless he wilfully absents himself, shall`
  line `divide the sample into four portions and effectively seal and suitably mark the same and permit`
  line `such person to add his own seal and mark to all or any of the portions so sealed and marked:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the sample is taken from premises whereon the drug ^1[or cosmetic]`
  line `is being manufactured, it shall be necessary to divide the sample into three portions only:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the drug ^1[or cosmetic] is made up in containers of small`
  line `volume, instead of dividing a sample as aforesaid, the Inspector may, and if the drug ^1[or`
  line `cosmetic] be such that it is likely to deteriorate or be otherwise damaged by exposure shall,`
  line `take three or four, as the case may be, of the said containers after suitably ma rking the same`
  line `and, where necessary, sealing them.`
  line
  line `(4) The Inspector shall restore one portion of a sample so divided or one container, as the`
  line `case may be, to the person from whom he takes it, and shall retain the remainder and dispose of`
  line `the same as follows:--`
  line
  line `(i) one portion or container he shall forthwith send to the Government Analyst for test`
  line `or analysis;`
  line
  line `(ii) the second, he shall produce to the Court before which proceedings, if any, are`
  line `instituted in respect of the drug ^1[or cosmetic]; and`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) the third, where taken, he shall send to the person, if any, whose name, address`
  line `and other particulars have been disclosed under section 18A.]`
  line
  line `(5) Where an Inspector takes any action under clause (c) of section 22,--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall use all despatch in ascertaining whether or not the drug ^1`
  line `or cosmetic;`
  line
  line `contravenes any of the provisions of section 18 and, if it is ascertained that the drug ^1[or`
  line `cosmetic]; does not so contravene, forthwith revoke the order passed under the sa id`
  line `clause or, as the case may be, take such action as may be necessary for the return of the`
  line `stock seized;`
  line
  line `(b) if he seizes the stock of the drug ^1[or cosmetic]; he shall as soon as may be inform ^3[a Judicial`
  line `Magistrate] and take his orders as to the custody thereof;`
  line
  line `( c ) without prejudice to the institution of any prosecution, if the alleged contravention be such`
  line `that the defect may be remedied by the possessor of the drug ^4[or cosmetic]; he shall, on being`
  line `satisfied that the defect has been so remedied, forthwith revoke his order under the said clause.`
  line
  line `^5[(6) Where an Inspector seizes any record, register, document or any other material object under`
  line `clause (cc) of sub-section (1) of section 22, he shall, as soon as may be, inform ^6[a Judicial Magistrate]`
  line `and take his orders as to the custody thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 15 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 16, for cl. (iii) (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 20, for "a Magistrate" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 15 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 35 of 1960, s. 6 (w.e.f. 16-3-1961).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 20, for "a Magistrate" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (27642)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 38
  title `Persons bound to disclose place where drugs or cosmetics are manufactured or kept.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 15 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27642&sectionno=24&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every person for the time being in charge of any premises whereon any drug ^1[or`
  line `cosmetic]; is being manufactured or is kept for sale or distribution shall, on being required`
  line `by an Inspector so to do, be legally bound to disclose to the Inspector the place where the`
  line `drug ^1[or cosmetic] is being manufactured or is kept, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (27643)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 39
  title `Reports of Government Analysts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27643&sectionno=25&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government Analyst to whom a`
  line `sample of any drug ^1[or cosmetic] has been submitted for test or analysis under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 23, shall deliver to the Inspector submitting it a signed report in`
  line `triplicate in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(2) The Inspector on receipt thereof shall deliver one copy of the report to the person`
  line `from whom the sample was taken ^2[and another copy to the person, if any, whose name,`
  line `address and other particulars have been disclosed under section 18A], and shall retain the`
  line `third copy for use in any prosecution in respect of the sample.`
  line
  line `(3) Any document purporting to be a report signed by a Government Analyst under this`
  line `Chapter shall be evidence of the facts stated therein, and such evidence shall be conclusive`
  line `unless the person from whom the sample was taken ^3[or the person whose name, address and`
  line `other particulars have been disclosed under section 18A] has, within twenty -eight days of the`
  line `receipt of a copy of the report, notified in writing the Inspector or the Court before which any`
  line `proceedings in respect of the sample are pending that he intends to adduce evidence in`
  line `controversion of the report.`
  line
  line `(4) Unless the sample has already been tested or analysed in the Central Drugs Laboratory,`
  line `where a person has under sub-section (3) notified his intention of adducing evidence in`
  line `controversion of a Government Analyst's report, the Court may, of its own motion or in its`
  line `discretion at the request either of the complainant or the accused cause the sample of the drug`
  line `^1[or cosmetic] produced before the Magistrate under sub-section (4) of section 23 to be sent for`
  line `test or analysis to the said Laboratory, which shall make the test or analysis and report in`
  line `writing signed by or under the authority of, the Director of the Central Drugs Laboratory the`
  line `result thereof, and such report shall be conclusive evidence of the facts stated therein.`
  line
  line `(5) The cost of a test or analysis made by the Central Drugs Laboratory under`
  line `sub-section (4) shall be paid by the complainant or accused as the Court shall direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 15 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 17, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "or the said warrantor" (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (27644)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 40
  title `Purchaser of drug or cosmetic enabled to obtain test or analysis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27644&sectionno=26&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `^2[or any recognised consumer association, whether such person is a member of that association`
  line `or not,] shall, on application in the prescribed manner and on payment of the prescribed fee, be`
  line `entitled to submit for test or analysis to a Government Analyst any drug ^1[or cosmetic]`
  line `^3[purchased by him or it] and to receive a report of such test or analysis signed by the`
  line `Government Analyst.`
  line
  line `^4 [Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 32, "recognised consumer association`
  line `means a voluntary consumer association registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 15 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 71 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-9-1987).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "purchased by him" (w.e.f. 15-9-1987).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 71 of 1986, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-9-1987)`
obj_root_law_sections_26_a:
  sectionId (27645)
  sectionNo 26A
  orderNo 41
  title `Powers of Central Government to regulate, restrict or prohibit manufacture, etc., of drug and cosmetic in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27645&sectionno=26A&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[26A. Powers of Central Government to ^2[regulate, restrict or prohibit] manufacture, etc.,`
  line `of drug and cosmetic in public interest.-- Without prejudice to any other provision contained in this`
  line `Chapter, if the Central Government is satisfied, that the use of any drug or cosmetic is likely to`
  line `involve any risk to human beings or animals or that any drug does not have the therapeutic value`
  line `claimed or purported to be claimed for it or contains ingredients and in such quantity for which there`
  line `is no therapeutic justification and that in the public interest it is necessary or expedient so to do, then,`
  line `that Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, ^2[regulate, restrict or prohibit] the`
  line `manufacture, sale or distribution of such drug or cosmetic.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982. s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 4, for "prohibit" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_b:
  sectionId (27646)
  sectionNo 26B
  orderNo 42
  title `Powers of Central Government to regulate or restrict, manufacture, etc., of drug in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content
  footnotes `1. 4. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27646&sectionno=26B&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[26B. Power of Central Government to regulate or restrict, manufacture, etc., of drug in`
  line `public interest. --Without prejudice to any other provision contained in this Chapter, if the Central`
  line `Government is satisfied that a drug is essential to meet the requirements of an emergency arising due to`
  line `epidemic or natural calamities and that in the public interest, it is necessary or expedient so to do, then,`
  line `that Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, regulate or restrict the manufacture, sale or`
  line `distribution of such drug.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (27647)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 43
  title `Penalty for manufacture, sale, etc., of drugs in contravention of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27647&sectionno=27&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Penalty for manufacture, sale, etc., of drugs in contravention of this`
  line `Chapter.--Whoever, himself or by any other person on his behalf, manufactures for sale or for`
  line `distribution, or sells, or stocks or exhibits or offers for sale or distributes,--`
  line
  line `(a) any drug deemed to be adulterated under section 17A or spurious under section ^2[17B`
  line `and which] when used by any person for or in the diagnosis, treatment, mitigation, or pre -`
  line `vention of any disease or disorder is likely to cause his death or is likely to cause such harm on`
  line `his body as would amount to grevious hurt within the meaning of section 320 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860) solely on account of such drug being adulterated or spurious or not of`
  line `standard quality, as the case may be, shall be ^3[punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `shall not be less than ten years but which may extend to imprisonment for life and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees or three times value of the drugs`
  line `confiscated, whichever is more]:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the fine imposed on and released from, the person convicted under this`
  line `clause shall be paid, by way of compensation, to the person who had used the adulterated or`
  line `spurious drugs referred to in this clause:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the use of the adulterated or, spurious drugs referred to in this clause`
  line `has caused the death of a person who used such drugs, the fine imposed on and realised from, the`
  line `person convicted under this clause, shall be paid to the relative of the person who had died due to the`
  line `use of the adulterated or spurious drugs referred to in this clause.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of the second proviso, the expression "relative" means--`
  line
  line `(i) spouse of the deceased person; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a minor legitimate son, and unmarried legitimate daughter and a widowed mother; or`
  line
  line `(iii) parent of the minor victim; or`
  line
  line `(iv) if wholly dependent on the earnings of the deceased person at the time of his death, a son or a`
  line `daughter who has attained the age of eighteen years; or`
  line
  line `(v) any person, if wholly or in part, dependent on the earnings of the deceased person at the`
  line `time of his death,--`
  line
  line `(a) the parent; or`
  line
  line `(b) a minor brother or an unmarried sister; or`
  line
  line `(c) a widowed daughter-in-law; or`
  line
  line `(d) a widowed sister; or`
  line
  line `(e) a minor child of a pre-deceased son; or`
  line
  line `(f) a minor child of a pre-deceased daughter where no parent of the child is alive; or`
  line
  line `(g) the paternal grandparent if no parent of the member is alive;]`
  line
  line `(b) any drug--`
  line
  line `(i) deemed to be adulterated under section 17A but not being a drug referred to in clause (a),`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) without a valid licence as required under clause (c) of section 18,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall ^5[not be less than three years`
  line `but which may extend to five years and with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees`
  line `or three times the value of the drugs confiscated, whichever is more]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be recorded in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of ^6[less than three years and of fine of less than one`
  line `lakh rupees];`
  line
  line `(c) any drug deemed to be spurious under section 17B, but not being a drug referred to in`
  line `clause (a) shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall ^7[not less than seven years`
  line `but which may extend to imprisonment for life and with fine which shall not be three lakh rupees or`
  line `three times the value of the drugs confiscated, whichever is more]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be recorded in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of ^8[less than seven years but not less than three years`
  line `and of fine of less than one lakh rupees];`
  line
  line `(d) any drug, other than a drug referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c),`
  line `in contravention of any other provision of this Chapter or any rule made thereunder, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may`
  line `extend to two years ^9[and with fine which shall not be less than twenty thousand rupees]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be recorded in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than one year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 22, for sections 27 and 27A (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 6, for "17B or which" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend`
  line `to a term of life and with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees;" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `4. The provisos ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 6, for "not be less than one year but which may extend to three years and with fine which shall not`
  line `be less than five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "less than one year and of fine of less than five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "not be less than three years but which may extend to five years and with fine which shall not be less`
  line `than five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "less than three years but not less than one year" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "and with fine" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (27648)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 44
  title `Penalty for manufacture, sale, etc., of cosmetics in contravention of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27648&sectionno=27A&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Penalty for manufacture, sale, etc., of cosmetics in contravention of this`
  line `Chapter.--Whoever himself or by any other person on his behalf manufactures for sale or for`
  line `distribution, or sells, or stocks or exhibits or offers for sale--`
  line
  line `^2[(i) any cosmetic deemed to be spurious under section 17D or adulterated under section 17E`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees or three times the value of the cosmetics`
  line `confiscated, whichever is more;`
  line
  line `(ii) any cosmetic other than a cosmetic referred to in clause (i) in contravention of any provisions`
  line `of this Chapter or any rule made thereunder shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to one year or with fine which may extend to twenty thousand rupees, or with both.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 22, for sections 27 and 27A (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for clauses (i) and (ii) (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (27649)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 45
  title `Penalty for non-disclosure of the name of the manufacturer, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27649&sectionno=28&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[28. Penalty for non-disclosure of the name of the manufacturer, etc.--Whoever`
  line `contravenes the provisions of section 18A ^2[or section 24] shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or ^3[with fine which shall not be less`
  line `than twenty thousand rupees or with both].]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs, by Act 13 of 1964, s. 19, for s. 28 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 8, for "with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees or with both" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (27650)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 46
  title `Penalty for not keeping documents, etc., and for non-disclosure of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27650&sectionno=28A&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[28A. Penalty for not keeping documents, etc., and for non-disclosure of`
  line `information.-- Whoever without reasonable cause or excuse, contravenes the provisions of`
  line `section 18B shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or`
  line `^2[with fine which shall not be less than twenty thousand rupees or with both].`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982 s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 8, for "with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees or with both" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b:
  sectionId (27651)
  sectionNo 28B
  orderNo 47
  title `Penalty for manufacture, etc., of drugs or cosmetics in contravention of section 26A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982 s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27651&sectionno=28B&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[28B. Penalty for manufacture, etc., of drugs or cosmetics in contravention of`
  line `section 26A.--Whoever himself or by any other person on his behalf manufactures or sells or`
  line `distributes any drug or cosmetic in contravention of the provisions of any notification issued`
  line `under section 26A, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (27652)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 48
  title `Penalty for use of Government Analyst’s report for advertising.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27652&sectionno=29&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Whoever uses any`
  line `report of a test or analysis made by the Central Drugs Laboratory or by a Government Analyst,`
  line `or any extract from such report, for the purpose of advertising any drug ^1[or cosmetic], shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to ^2[five thousand rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 15 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 10, for "five hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009)`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (27653)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 49
  title `Penalty for subsequent offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27653&sectionno=30&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Penalty for subsequent offences.--`
  line `^2[(1) Whoever having been convicted of an`
  line offence,--
  line
  line `(a) under clause (b) of section 27 is again convicted of an offence under that`
  line `clause, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall ^3[not be less`
  line `than seven years but which may extend to ten years and with fine which shall not be`
  line `less than two lakh rupees]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment, impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of ^4[less than seven years and of`
  line `fine of less than one lakh rupees];`
  line
  line `(b) under clause (c) of section 27, is again convicted of an offence under that clause`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which ^5[shall not be less than ten years`
  line `but which may extend to imprisonment for life and with fine which shall not be less than`
  line `three lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `(c) under clause (d) of section 27, is again convicted of an offence under that clause shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than two years but which`
  line `may extend to four years or with fine which shall not be less than ^6[fifty thousand rupee, or`
  line `with both.`
  line
  line `^7[(1A) Whoever, having been convicted of an offence under section 27A is again convicted`
  line `under that section, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years, or with fine which may extend to ^8[two thousand rupees], or with both.]`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, having been convicted of an offence under ^9*** section 29 is again convicted of an`
  line `offence under the same section shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to ^10[two`
  line `years, or with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees or with both.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 14, for s. 30.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 25, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 11 for "not be less than two years but which may extend to six years and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than ten thousand rupees"(w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "less than two years and of fine of less than ten thousand rupees (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "shall not be less than six years but which may extend to ten years and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than ten thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 20 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 25, for "one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `9. The words and figures "section 28 or" omitted by Act 13 of 1964, s. 20 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 11, for "ten years or with fine or with both" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (27654)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 50
  title Confiscation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27654&sectionno=31&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where any person has been convicted under this Chapter for`
  line `contravening any such provision of this Chapter or any rule made thereunder as may be`
  line `specified by rule made in this behalf, the stock of the drug ^2[or cosmetic] in respect of which`
  line `the contravention has been made shall be liable to confiscation ^3[and if such contravention is in`
  line `respect of--`
  line
  line `^4[(i) manufacture of any drug deemed to be misbranded under section 17, adulterated under`
  line `section 17A or spurious under section 17B; or]`
  line
  line `(ii)`
  line `^5[manufacture for sale, or for distribution, sale, or stocking, or exhibiting or offering`
  line `for sale,] or distribution of any drug without a valid licence as required under clause (c) of`
  line `section 18,`
  line
  line `any implements or machinery used in such manufacture, sale or distribution and any receptacles`
  line `packages or coverings in which such drug is contained and the animals, vehicles, vessels`
  line `or other conveyances used in carrying such drug shall also be liable to confiscation.`
  line
  line `^6[(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), where the Court is`
  line `satisfied, on the application of an Inspector or otherwise and after such inquiry as may be`
  line `necessary that the drug or cosmetic is not of standard quality ^7[or is a ^5[`
  line `misbranded, adulterated`
  line `or spurious drug or misbranded or spurious cosmetic,] such drug or, as the case may be, such`
  line `cosmetic shall be liable to confiscation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Re-numbered as sub-section (I) by Act 35 of 1960, s. 9 (w.e.f. 16-3-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 21 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 13 of 1964. s. 21 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 26, for cl. (i) (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 26, ibid" for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (2) ins. by Act 35 of 1960, s. 9, subs. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 21 (w. e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 13 of 1964. s. 21, for "or is a misbranded drug" (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (27655)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 51
  title `Application of provisions to Government departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 22. ibid. (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27655&sectionno=31A&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Application of provisions to Government departments.--The provisions of`
  line `this Chapter except those contained in section 31 shall apply in relation to the manufacture,`
  line `sale or distribution of drugs by any department of Government as they apply in relation to`
  line `the manufacture, sale or distribution of drugs by any other person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (27656)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 52
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 12, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27656&sectionno=32&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1 [(1) No prosecution under this Chapter shall be instituted except`
  line by--
  line
  line `(a) an Inspector; or`
  line
  line `(b) any gazetted officer of the Central Government or a State Government authorised in writing in`
  line `this behalf by the Central Government or a State Government or by a general or special order made in`
  line `this behalf by that Government; or`
  line
  line `(c) the person aggrieved; or`
  line
  line `(d) a recognised consumer association whether such person is a member of that association or`
  line not.
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, no court inferior to that of a Court of Session shall try an`
  line `offence punishable under this Chapter.]`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this Chapter shall be deemed to prevent any person from being`
  line `prosecuted under any other law for any act or omission which constitutes an offence against`
  line `this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (27657)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 53
  title `Power of Court to implead the manufacturer, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27657&sectionno=32A&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. Power of Court to implead the manufacturer, etc.--Where, at any time during the`
  line `trial of any offence under this Chapter alleged to have been committed by any person, not being`
  line `the manufacturer of a drug or cosmetic or his agent for the distribution thereof the Court is`
  line `satisfied, on the evidence adduced before it, that such manufacturer or agent is also concerned in`
  line `that offence, then, the Court may, notwithstanding anything contained ^2[in sub-sections (1), (2)`
  line `and (3) of section 319 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)], proceed against him`
  line `as though a prosecution had been instituted against him under section 32.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 23 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 28, for "in sub-section (1) of section 351 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b:
  sectionId (27658)
  sectionNo 32B
  orderNo 54
  title `Compounding of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 13 (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27658&sectionno=32B&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[32B. Compounding of certain offences. --(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973, (2 of 1974) any offence punishable under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13, section 28 and section 28A of this Act (whether committed by a company or any officer`
  line `thereof), not being an offence punishable with imprisonment only, or with imprisonment and also with fine,`
  line `may, either before or after the institution of any prosecution, be compounded by the Central Government or by`
  line `any State Government or any officer authorised in this behalf by the Central Government or a State`
  line `Government, on payment for credit to that Government of such sum as that Government may, by rules made`
  line `in this behalf, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that such sum shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the fine which may be`
  line `imposed under this Act for the offence so compounded:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in cases of subsequent offences, the same shall not be compoundable.`
  line
  line `(2) When the accused has been committed for trial or when he has been convicted and an appeal is`
  line `pending, no composition for the offence shall be allowed without, the leave of the court to which he is`
  line `committed or, as the case may be, before which the appeal is to be heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an offence is compounded under sub-section (1), no proceeding or further proceeding, as`
  line `the case may be, shall be taken against the offender in respect of the offence so compounded and the`
  line `offender, if in custody, shall be released forthwith.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (27659)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27659&sectionno=33&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Central Government may`
  line `^2[after consultation with, or on the recommendation of, the Board] and after previous publication`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions`
  line `of this Chapter :`
  line
  line `Provided that consultation with the Board may be dispensed with if the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that circumstances have arisen which render it necessary to make`
  line `rules without such consultation, but in such a case the Board shall be consulted within six`
  line `months of the making of the rules and the Central Government shall take into consideration`
  line `any suggestions which the Board may make in relation to the amendment of the said rules.]`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide for the establishment of laboratories for testing and analysing drugs ^3[or`
  line cosmetics];
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the qualifications and duties of Government Analysts and the`
  line `qualifications of Inspectors;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe the methods of test or analysis to be employed in determining whether a drug ^3[or`
  line `cosmetic] is of standard quality;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribe, in respect of biological and organometallic compounds, the units or methods of`
  line standardisation;
  line
  line `^4[(dd) prescribe under clause (d) of ^5[section 17A] the colour or colours which a drug may bear`
  line `or contain for purposes of colouring;]`
  line
  line `^6[(dda) prescribe under clause (d) of section 17E the colour or colours which a cosmetic may`
  line `bear or contain for the purposes of colouring];`
  line
  line `(e) prescribe the forms of licences ^7[for the manufacture for sale or for distribution], for the sale`
  line `and for the distribution of drugs or any specified drug or class of drugs ^8[or of cosmetics or any`
  line `specified cosmetic or class of cosmetics], the form of application for such licences, the conditions`
  line `subject to which such licences may be issued, the authority empowered to issue the same ^9[the`
  line `qualifications of such authority] and the fees payable therefor ^9[and provide for the cancellation or`
  line `suspension of such licences in any case where any provision of this Chapter or the rules made`
  line `thereunder is contravened or any of the conditions subject to which they are issued is not complied`
  line with];
  line
  line `^9[(ee) prescribe the records, registers or other documents to be kept and maintained under`
  line `section 18B;`
  line
  line `(eea) prescribe the fees for the inspection (for the purposes of grant or renewal of licences) of`
  line `premises, wherein any drug or cosmetic is being or is proposed to be manufactured;`
  line
  line `(eeb) prescribe the manner in which copies are to be certified under sub-section (2A) of`
  line `section 22;]`
  line
  line `(f) specify the diseases or ailments which a drug may not purport or claim ^10[to prevent`
  line `cure or mitigate] and such other effects which a drug may not purport or claim to have;`
  line
  line `(g) prescribe the conditions subject to which small quantities of drugs may be`
  line `manufactured for the purpose of examination, test or analysis;`
  line
  line `(h) require the date of manufacture and the date of expiry of potency to be clearly and`
  line `truly stated on the lable or container of any specified drug or class of drugs, and prohibit the`
  line `sale stocking or exhibition for sale, or distribution of the said drug or class of drugs after the`
  line `expiry of a specified period from the date of manufacture or after the expiry of the date of`
  line potency;
  line
  line `(i) prescribe the conditions to be observed in the packing in bottles, packages and other containers`
  line `of drugs ^11[or cosmetics], ^12[including the use of packing material which comes into direct contact with`
  line `the drugs] and prohibit the sale, stocking or exhibition for sale, or distribution of drugs`
  line `^11[or cosmetics], packed in contravention of such conditions;`
  line
  line `(j) regulate the mode of labelling packed drugs ^11[or cosmetics], and prescribe the`
  line `matters which shall or shall not be included in such labels;`
  line
  line `(k) prescribe the maximum proportion of any poisonous substance which may be added to or`
  line `contained in any drug, prohibit the manufacture, sale or stocking or exhibition for sale, or distribution`
  line `of any drug in which that proportion is exceeded, and specify substances which shall be deemed to be`
  line `poisonous for the purposes of this Chapter and the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(l) require that the accepted scientific name of any specified drug shall be displayed in`
  line `the prescribed manner on the lable or wrapper of any patent or proprietary medicine containing such drug;`
  line
  line `^13* * * * *`
  line
  line `^14[(n) prescribe the powers and duties of Inspectors ^12[and the qualifications of the authority to`
  line `which such Inspectors shall be subordinate] and ^15[specify the drugs or classes of drugs of cosmetics`
  line `or classes of cosmetics] in relation to which and the conditions, limitations or restrictions subject to`
  line `which, such powers and duties may be exercised or performed;]`
  line
  line `(o) prescribe the forms of report to be given by Government Analysts, and the manner of`
  line `application for test or analysis under section 26 and the fees payable therefor;`
  line
  line `^16[(p) specify the offences against this Chapter or any rule made thereunder in relation to which an`
  line `order of confiscation may be made under section 31;`
  line ^17***]
  line
  line `(q) provide for the exemption conditionally or otherwise, from all or any of the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter or the rules made thereunder, of any specified drug or class of drugs`
  line `^11[or cosmetic or class of`
  line cosmetics]
  line ^18[and];
  line
  line `^19[(r) sum which may be specified by the Central Government under section 32B.]`
  line
  line `^20* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 15, for sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 29, for "after consultation with the Board" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 22 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 24 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 29, for "section 17B" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 14 (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 29, for "for the manufacture for sale" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 22 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 15, for "to cure or mitigate".`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 22 (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `13. Cl. (m) omitted by Act 13 of 1964, s. 24 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 35 of 1960, s. 10, for cl. (n) (w.e.f. 16-3-1961).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 21 of 1962, s. 22, for "the drugs or class of drugs" (w.e.f. 27-7-1964).`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 24, for cl. (p) (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `17. The word "and" omitted by Act 26 of 2008, s. 14 (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `18. Ins. by, s. 14 ibid. (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `19. Ins. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 14 (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `20. Sub-section (3) ins. by Act 35 of 1960, omitted by Act 13 of 1964, s. 24 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (27660)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 56
  title `Chapter not to apply to Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27660&sectionno=33A&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[33A. Chapter not to apply to Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drugs.-- Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act, nothing contained in this Chapter shall apply to ^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha`
  line `or Unani] drugs.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_b:
  sectionId (27661)
  sectionNo 33B
  orderNo 57
  title `Application of Chapter IVA`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27661&sectionno=33B&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[33B. Application of Chapter IVA.--This Chapter shall apply only to ^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha and`
  line `Unani] drugs.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_c:
  sectionId (27662)
  sectionNo 33C
  orderNo 58
  title `Ayurvedic and Unani Drugs Technical Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27662&sectionno=33C&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[33C. Ayurvedic and Unani Drugs Technical Advisory Board. --(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, by notification in the Official Gazette and with effect from such date as may be specified therein,`
  line `constitute a Board (to be called the ^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani Drugs Technical Advisory Board]) to`
  line `advise the Central Government and the State Governments on Technical matters arising out of this`
  line `Chapter and to carry out the other functions assigned to it by this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely: --`
  line
  line `(i) the Director General of Health Services ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Drugs Controller, India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `^3[(iii) the principal officer dealing with Indian systems of medicine in the Ministry of Health,`
  line `ex officio];`
  line
  line `(iv) the Director of the Central Drugs Laboratory, Calcutta ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) one person holding the appointment of Government Analyst under section 33F, to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(vi) one Pharmacognocist to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(vii) one Phyto-chemist to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `^4[(viii) four persons to be nominated by the Central Government, two from amongst the members`
  line `of the Ayurvedic Pharmacopoeia Committee, one from amongst the members of the Unani`
  line `Pharmacopoeia Committee and one from amongst the members of the Siddha Pharmacopoeia`
  line Committee;]
  line
  line `(ix) one teacher in Darvyaguna, and Bhaishajya Kalpana, to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(x) one teacher in ILM-UL-ADVIA and TAKLIS-WA-DAWASAZI, to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `^5[(xi) one teacher in Gunapadam to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xii) three persons, one each to represent the Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani drug industry, to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xiii) three persons, one each from among the practitioners of Ayurvedic, Siddha`
  line `and Unani Tibb systems of medicine to be nominated by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall appoint a member of the Board as its Chairman.`
  line
  line `(4) The nominated members of the Board shall hold office for three years but shall be eligible for`
  line renomination.
  line
  line `(5) The Board may, subject to the previous approval of the Central Government, make bye -`
  line `laws fixing a quorum and regulating its own procedure and conduct of all business to be tran -`
  line `sacted by it.`
  line
  line `(6) The functions of the Board may be exercised notwithstanding any vacancy therein.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government shall appoint a person to be Secretary of the Board and`
  line `shall provide the Board with such clerical and other staff as the Central Government`
  line `considers necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 30, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for cl. (iii) (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 30, for cl. (viii) (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for cls. (xi) and (xii) (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_d:
  sectionId (27663)
  sectionNo 33D
  orderNo 59
  title `The Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani Drugs Consultative Committee`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sections.33D and 33E (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27663&sectionno=33D&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[33D. The Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani Drugs Consultative Committee.--(1) The`
  line `Central Government may constitute an Advisory Committee to be called the Ayurvedic,`
  line `Siddha and Unani Drugs Consultative Committee to advise the Central Government, the State`
  line `Governments and the Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani Drugs Technical Advisory Board on any`
  line `matter for the purpose of securing uniformity throughout India in the administration of this`
  line `Act in so far as it relates to Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drugs.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani Drugs Consultative Committee shall consist of two`
  line `persons to be nominated by the Central Government as representatives of that Government`
  line `and not more than one representative of each State to be nominated by the State Government`
  line concerned.
  line
  line `(3) The Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani Drugs Consultative Committee shall meet when`
  line `required to do so by the Central Government and shall regulate its own procedure.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_e:
  sectionId (27664)
  sectionNo 33E
  orderNo 60
  title `Misbranded drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_e_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sections.33D and 33E (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27664&sectionno=33E&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[33E. Misbranded drugs.--For the purposes of this Chapter, an Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug`
  line `shall be deemed to be misbranded--`
  line
  line `(a) if it is so coloured, coated, powdered or polished that damage is concealed, or if`
  line `it is made to appear of better or greater therapeutic value than it really is; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is not labelled in the prescribed manner; or`
  line
  line `(c) if its label or container or anything accompanying the drug bears any statement,`
  line `design or device which makes any false claim for the drug or which is false or misleading in`
  line `any particular.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_ee:
  sectionId (27665)
  sectionNo 33EE
  orderNo 61
  title `Adulterated drugs`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_ee_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sections.33D and 33E (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27665&sectionno=33EE&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_ee_content:
  string
  line `^1[33EE. Adulterated drugs.--For the purposes of this Chapter, an Ayurvedic, Siddha or`
  line `Unani drug shall be deemed to be adulterated,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it consists, in whole or in part, of any filthy, putrid or decomposed substance;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) if it has been prepared, packed or stored under insanitary conditions whereby it`
  line `may have been contaminated with filth or whereby it may have been rendered injurious to`
  line `health; or`
  line
  line `(c) if its container is composed, in whole or in part, of any poisonous or deleterious`
  line `substance which may render the contents injurious to health; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it bears or contains, for purposes of colouring only, a colour other than one which is`
  line `prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it contains any harmful or toxic substance which may render it injurious to`
  line `health; or`
  line
  line `(f) if any substance has been mixed therewith so as to reduce its quality or strength.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of clause (a), a drug shall not be deemed to consist, in whole`
  line `or in part, of any decomposed substance only by reason of the fact that such decomposed`
  line `substance is the result of any natural decomposition of the drug:`
  line
  line `Provided that such decomposition is not due to any negligence on the part of the manufac -`
  line `turer of the drug or the dealer thereof and that it does not render the drug injurious to health.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_eea:
  sectionId (27666)
  sectionNo 33EEA
  orderNo 62
  title `Spurious drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_eea_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sections.33D and 33E (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27666&sectionno=33EEA&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_eea_content:
  string
  line `^1[33EEA. Spurious drugs.--For the purposes of this Chapter, an Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug`
  line `shall be deemed to be spurious--`
  line
  line `(a) if it is sold, or offered or exhibited for sale, under a name which belongs to another`
  line `drug; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it is an imitation of, or is substitute for, another drug or resembles another drug in`
  line `a manner likely to deceive, or bears upon it or upon its label or container the name of`
  line `another drug, unless it is plainly and conspicuously marked so as to reveal its true chara cter`
  line `and its lack of identity with such other drug; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the label or container bears the name of an individual or company purporting to be the`
  line `manufacturer of the drug, which individual or company is fictitious or does not exist; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it has been substituted wholly or in part by any other drug or substance; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it purports to be the product of a manufacturer of whom it is not truly a product.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_eeb:
  sectionId (27667)
  sectionNo 33EEB
  orderNo 63
  title `Regulation of manufacture for sale of Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani drugs`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_eeb_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sections.33D and 33E (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27667&sectionno=33EEB&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_eeb_content:
  string
  line `^1[33EEB. Regulation of manufacture for sale of Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani drugs.--No`
  line `person shall manufacture for sale or for distribution any Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani drug except`
  line `in accordance with such standards, if any, as may be prescribed in relation to that drug.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_eec:
  sectionId (27668)
  sectionNo 33EEC
  orderNo 64
  title `Prohibition of manufacture and sale of certain Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani drugs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_eec_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sections.33D and 33E (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27668&sectionno=33EEC&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_eec_content:
  string
  line `^1[33EEC. Prohibition of manufacture and sale of certain Ayurvedic, Siddha and Unani`
  line `drugs.--From such date as the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify in this behalf, no person, either by himself or by any other person on his behalf, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) manufacture for sale or for distribution--`
  line
  line `(i) any misbranded, adulterated or spurious Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug;`
  line
  line `(ii) any patent or proprietary medicine, unless there is displayed in the prescribed`
  line `manner on the label or container thereof the true list of all the ingredients contained in it;`
  line and
  line
  line `(iii) any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug in contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter or any rule made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) sell, stock or exhibit or offer for sale or distribute any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug`
  line `which has been manufactured in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act, or any rule made`
  line thereunder,
  line
  line `(c) manufacture for sale or for distribution, any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug except under,`
  line `and in accordance with the conditions of, a licence issued for such purpose under this Chapter by the`
  line `prescribed authority :`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to Vaidyas and Hakims who manufacture Ayurvedic,`
  line `Siddha or Unani drug for the use of their own patients :`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this section shall apply to the manufacture, subject to the prescribed`
  line `conditions, of small quantities of any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug for the purpose of examination,`
  line `test or analysis.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_eed:
  sectionId (27669)
  sectionNo 33EED
  orderNo 65
  title `Power of Central Government to prohibit manufacture, etc., of Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drugs in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_eed_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sections.33D and 33E (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27669&sectionno=33EED&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_eed_content:
  string
  line `^1[33EED. Power of Central Government to prohibit manufacture, etc., of Ayurvedic,`
  line `Siddha or Unani drugs in public interest.--Without prejudice to any other provision contained in`
  line `this Chapter, if the Central Government is satisfied on the basis of any evidence or other material`
  line `available before it that the use of any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug is likely to involve any risk`
  line `to human being or animals or that any such drug does not have the therapeutic value claimed or`
  line `purported to be claimed for it and that in the public interest it is necessary or expendient so to do`
  line `then, that Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, prohibit the manufacture, sale`
  line `or distribution of such drug.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_f:
  sectionId (27670)
  sectionNo 33F
  orderNo 66
  title `Government Analysts`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27670&sectionno=33F&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[33F. Government Analysts.--(1) The Central Government or a State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint such persons as it thinks fit, having the prescribed`
  line `qualifications, to be Government Analysts for such areas as may be assigned to them by the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), neither the Central Government nor`
  line `a State Government shall appoint as a Government Analysts any official not serving under it`
  line `without the previous consent of the Government under which he is serving.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) No person who has any financial interest in the manufacture or sale of any drug shall be`
  line `appointed to be a Government Analysts under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `3. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for sections.33D and 33E (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_g:
  sectionId (27671)
  sectionNo 33G
  orderNo 67
  title Inspectors.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27671&sectionno=33G&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[33G. Inspectors.--(1) The Central Government or a State Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint such persons as it thinks fit, having the prescribed qualifications to be Inspectors`
  line `for such areas as may be assigned to them by the Central Government or the State Government, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers which may be exercised by an Inspector and the duties which may be`
  line `performed by him and the conditions, limitations or restrictions subject to which such powers`
  line `and duties may be exercised or performed shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) No person who has any financial interest in the manufacture or sale of any drug shall be appointed`
  line `to be an Inspector under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Inspector shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and shall be officially subordinate to such authority as`
  line `the Government appointing him may specify in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_h:
  sectionId (27672)
  sectionNo 33H
  orderNo 68
  title `Application of provisions of sections 22, 23, 24 and 25.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27672&sectionno=33H&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[33H. Application of provisions of sections 22, 23, 24 and 25.--The provisions of`
  line `sections 22, 23, 24 and 25 and the rules, if any, made thereunder shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to an Inspector and a Government Analyst appointed under this Chapter as they apply in`
  line `relation to an Inspector and a Government Analyst appointed under Chapter IV, subject to the`
  line `modification that the references to "drug" in the said sections, shall be construed as references to`
  line `^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drug.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_h_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `2 . Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_33_i:
  sectionId (27673)
  sectionNo 33-I
  orderNo 69
  title `Penalty for manufacture, sale, etc., of Ayurvedic. Siddha or Unani drug in contravention of this Chapter`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27673&sectionno=33-I&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[33-I. Penalty for manufacture, sale, etc., of Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug in contravention`
  line `of this Chapter.-- Whoever himself or by any other person on his behalf--`
  line
  line `(1) manufactures for sale or for distribution,--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug--`
  line
  line `(i) deemed to be misbranded under section 33E,`
  line
  line `(ii) deemed to be adulterated under section 33EE, or`
  line
  line `(iii) without a valid licence or in violation of any of the conditions thereof, as required`
  line `under section 33 EEC,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than twenty thousand rupees or three times the value of the drugs confiscated,`
  line `whichever is more;`
  line
  line `(b) any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug deemed to be spurious under`
  line `section 33EEA, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than one year but which may extend to three years and with fine which shall not be`
  line `less than ^188`
  line `fifty thousand rupees or three times the value of the drugs confiscated, whichever is`
  line `more:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for any adequate and special reas ons to be mentioned`
  line `in the judgment, impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than one year`
  line `and of fine of less than ^3[fifty thousand rupees or three times the value of the drugs`
  line `confiscated, whichever is more]; or`
  line
  line `^4(c) any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug in contravention of the provisions of any`
  line `notification issued under section 33EED shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to three years and with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees or three times`
  line `the value of the drugs confiscated, whichever is more.]`
  line
  line `(2) Contravenes any other provisions of this Chapter or of section 24 as applied by`
  line `section 33H or any rule made under this Chapter, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ^5[six months and with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand`
  line rupees].]
obj_root_law_sections_33_i_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for sections 33-I and 33J (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 15, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "three months and with fine which shall not be less than five hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_j:
  sectionId (27674)
  sectionNo 33J
  orderNo 70
  title `Penalty for subsequent offences`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_j_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_j_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27674&sectionno=33J&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[33J. Penalty for subsequent offences.--Whoever having been convicted of an offence,--`
  line
  line `(a) under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 33-I is again convicted of an offence`
  line `under that clause, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `two years and with fine which shall not be less than ^2[fifty thousand rupees or three times the`
  line `value of the drugs confiscated, whichever is more];`
  line
  line `(b) under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 33-I is again convicted of an offence`
  line `under that clause, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than two years but which may be extend to six years and with fine which shall not be less`
  line `than ^3[one lakh rupees or three times the value of the drugs confiscated, whichever is more]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in`
  line `the judgment, impose a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than two years and of`
  line `fine of less than ^3[one lakh rupees or three times the value of the drugs confiscated, whichever is`
  line more];
  line
  line `(c) under sub-section (2) of section 33-I is again convicted of an offence under that`
  line `sub-section, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^4[one`
  line `year and with fine which shall not be less than twenty thousand rupees or three times the value of the`
  line `drugs confiscated, whichever, is more].]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_j_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for sections 33-I and 33J (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs, by s. 16, ibid., for "two thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008 s. 16, for "five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "six months and with fine which shall not be less than one thousand rupees "`
  line `(w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_k:
  sectionId (27675)
  sectionNo 33K
  orderNo 71
  title Confiscation
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27675&sectionno=33K&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[33K. Confiscation.--Where any person has been convicted under this Chapter, the stock of`
  line `the ^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drug, in respect of which the contravention has been made,`
  line `shall be liable to confiscation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_k_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for sections 33-I and 33J (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_ka:
  sectionId (27676)
  sectionNo 33KA
  orderNo 72
  title `Disclosure of name of manufacturer, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_ka_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 17 (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27676&sectionno=33KA&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_ka_content:
  string
  line `^1[33KA. Disclosure of name of manufacturer, etc. -- Every person, not being the manufacturer`
  line `of any Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug or his agent for the distribution thereof, shall, if so required,`
  line `disclose to the Inspector the name, address and .`
  line `other particulars of the person from whom he acquired the`
  line `Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_kb:
  sectionId (27677)
  sectionNo 33KB
  orderNo 73
  title `Maintenance of records and furnishing of informantion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_kb_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 17 (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27677&sectionno=33KB&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_kb_content:
  string
  line `^1[33KB. Maintenance of records and furnishing of information. -- Every person holding a licence`
  line `under clause (c) of section 33EEC shall keep and maintain such records, registers and other documents as`
  line `may be prescribed and shall furnish to any officer or authority exercising any power or discharging any`
  line `function under this Act such information as is required by such officer or authority for carrying out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_l:
  sectionId (27678)
  sectionNo 33L
  orderNo 74
  title `Application of provisions to Government departments`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_l_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27678&sectionno=33L&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_l_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this`
  line `Chapter except those contained in section 33K shall apply in relation to the manufacture for sale,`
  line `sale, or distribution of any ^1[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drug by any department of`
  line `Government as they apply in relation to the manufacture for sale, sale, or distribution of such`
  line `drug by any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_m:
  sectionId (27679)
  sectionNo 33M
  orderNo 75
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_m_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_m_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27679&sectionno=33M&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[33M. Cognizance of offences.--(1) No prosecution under this Chapter shall be instituted`
  line `except by an Inspector ^2[with the previous sanction of the authority specified under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 33G].`
  line
  line `(2) No Court inferior to that ^3[of a Metropolitan Magistrate or of a Judicial Magistrate`
  line `of the first class] shall try an offence punishable under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_m_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for "of a Presidency Magistrate or of a Magistrate of the first class" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_33_n:
  sectionId (27680)
  sectionNo 33N
  orderNo 76
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_n_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_n_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27680&sectionno=33N&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[33N. Power of Central Government to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `^3[after consultation with, or on the recommendation of, the Board] and after previous publication`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions`
  line `of this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that consultation with the Board may be dispensed with if the Central Government is of`
  line `opinion that circumstances have arisen which render it necessary to make rules without such consultation,`
  line `but in such a case, the Board shall be consulted within six months of the making of the rules and the`
  line `Central Government shall take into consideration any suggestions which the Board may make in relation`
  line `to the amendment of the said rules.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide for the establishment of laboratories for testing and analysing ^2[Ayurvedic, Siddha or`
  line `Unani] drugs;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the qualifications and duties of Government Analysts and the`
  line `qualifications of Inspectors;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribe the methods of test or analysis to be employed in determining whether any`
  line `^4[Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani] drug is labelled with the true list of the ingredients which it is`
  line `purported to contain:`
  line
  line `(d) specify any substance as a poisonous substance;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribe the forms of licences for the manufacture for sale of ^4[Ayurvedic, Siddha or`
  line `Unani] drugs ^5[and for sale of processed Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drugs,] the form of`
  line `application for such licences, the conditions subject to which such licences may be issued,`
  line `the authority empowered to issue the same and the fees payable therefor; ^5[and provide for`
  line `the cancellation or suspension of such licences in any case where any provision of this`
  line `Chapter or rules made thereunder is contravened or any of the conditions subject to which`
  line `they are issued is not complied with];`
  line
  line `^6[(f) prescribe the conditions to be observed in the packing of Ayurvedic, Siddha and`
  line `Unani drugs including the use of packing material which comes into direct contact with the`
  line `drugs, regulate the mode of labelling packed drugs and prescribe the matters which shall or`
  line `shall not be included in such labels;]`
  line
  line `(g) prescribe the conditions subject to which small quantities of ^4[Ayurvedic, Siddha`
  line `or Unani] drugs may be manufactured for the purpose of examination, test or analysis;`
  line and
  line
  line `^7[(gg) prescribe under clause (d) of section 33EE the colour or colours which an`
  line `Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drug may bear or contain for purposes of colouring;`
  line
  line `(gga) prescribe the standards for Ayurvedic, Siddha or Unani drugs under`
  line `section 33EB;]`
  line
  line `^8[(ggb) prescribe the records, registers or the documents to be kept and`
  line `maintained under section 33KB; and]`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed under this Chapter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_n_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., "after consultation with the Board" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for cl. (f) (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 26 of 2008 s. 18 (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_o:
  sectionId (27681)
  sectionNo 33-O
  orderNo 77
  title `Power to amend First Schedule`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_o_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27681&sectionno=33-O&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[33-O. Power to amend First Schedule.--The Central Government, after consultation with`
  line `the Board and after giving, by notification in the Official Gazette, not less than three months`
  line `notice of its intention so to do, may, by a like notification, add to or otherwise amend the First`
  line `Schedule for the purposes of this Chapter and thereupon the said Schedule shall be deemed to`
  line `be amended accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_p:
  sectionId (27682)
  sectionNo 33P
  orderNo 78
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_p_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_p_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27682&sectionno=33P&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_33_p_content:
  string
  line ^1[^2[
  line `^3[33P.] Power to give directions.--The Central Government may give such directions`
  line `to any State Government as may appear to the Central Government to be necessary for`
  line `carrying into execution in the State any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or order`
  line `made thereunder.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_p_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 16, for s. 34.`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 35 of 1960, s. 11 (w.e.f. 16-3-1961).`
  line
  line `3 S. 33A re-numbered as s. 33P by Act 13 of 1964, s. 27 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964)`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (27683)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 79
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 16, for s. 34.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27683&sectionno=34&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Offences by companies.--(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of and was`
  line `responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against`
  line `and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable`
  line `to any punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed`
  line `without his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of`
  line `such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act`
  line `has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with`
  line `the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director,`
  line `manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_a:
  sectionId (27684)
  sectionNo 34A
  orderNo 80
  title `Offences by Government departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27684&sectionno=34A&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[34A. Offences by Government departments.--Where an offence under Chapter IV or`
  line `Chapter IVA has been committed by any department of Government, such authority as is`
  line `specified by the Central Government to be in charge of manufacture, sale, or distribution of`
  line `drugs or where no authority is specified, the head of the department shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall render any such authority or person`
  line `liable to any punishment provided in Chapter IV or Chapter IVA, as the case may be , if such`
  line `authority or person proves that the offence was committed without its or his knowledge or that`
  line `such authority or person exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such`
  line offence.]]
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 16, for s. 34.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 28 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_aa:
  sectionId (27685)
  sectionNo 34AA
  orderNo 81
  title `Penalty for vexatious search or seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_aa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_aa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27685&sectionno=34AA&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_34_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^1[34AA. Penalty for vexatious search or seizure.--Any Inspector exercising powers under this Act`
  line `or the rules made thereunder, who,--`
  line
  line `(a) without reasonable ground of suspicion searches any place, vehicle, vessel or other`
  line `conveyance; or`
  line
  line `(b) vexatiously and unnecessarily searches any person; or`
  line
  line `(c) vexatiously and unnecessarily seizes any drug or cosmetic, or any substance or`
  line `article, or any record, register, document or other material object; or`
  line
  line `(d) commits, as such Inspector, any other act, to the injury of any person without`
  line `having reason to believe that such act is require for the execution of his duty,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_aa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 16, for s. 34.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (27686)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 82
  title `Publication of sentences passed under this Act`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27686&sectionno=35&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person is convicted of an`
  line `offence under this Act, ^1[the Court before which the conviction takes place shall, on`
  line `application made to it by the Inspector cause] the offender's name, place of residence, the`
  line `offence of which he has been convicted and the penalty which has been inflicted upon him, to`
  line `be published at the expense of such person in such newspapers or in such other manner as the`
  line `Court may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The expenses of such publication shall be deemed to form part of the costs relating`
  line `to the conviction and shall be recoverable in the same manner as those costs are`
  line recoverable.
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (27687)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 83
  title `Magistrate’s power to impose enhanced penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27687&sectionno=36&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in ^1* * * ^2[the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)], it shall be lawful for`
  line `^3[any Metropolitan Magistrate or any Judicial Magistrate of the first class] to pass any`
  line `sentence authorized by this Act in excess of his powers under ^1* * * the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "section 32 of" omitted by Act 13 of 1964, s. 29 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 38, for "the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 38, ibid., for "any Presidency Magistrate or any Magistrate of the first class" (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_a:
  sectionId (27688)
  sectionNo 36A
  orderNo 84
  title `Certain offences to be tried summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27688&sectionno=36A&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[36A. Certain offences to be tried summarily.--Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), ^2[all offences (except the offences triable by`
  line `the Special Court under section 36AB or Court of Session under this Act] punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term not exceeding three years, other than an offence under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 33-I, shall be tried in a summary way by a Judicial Magistrate of the`
  line `first class specially empowered in this behalf by the State Government or by a Metropolitan`
  line `Magistrate and the provisions of sections 262 to 265 (both inclusive) of the said Code shall, as`
  line `far as may be, apply to such trial :`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section, it shall`
  line `be lawful for the Magistrate to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding`
  line `one year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when at the commencement of, or in the course of, a summary trial`
  line `under this section it appears to the Magistrate that the nature of the case is such that a sentence`
  line `of imprisonment for a term exceeding one year may have to be passed or that it is, for any other`
  line `reason, undesirable to try the case summarily, the Magistrate shall, after hearing the parties,`
  line `record an order to that effect and thereafter recall any witness who has been examined and`
  line `proceed to hear or rehear the case in the manner provided by the said Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 39, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 2008, s. 19, for "all offences under this Act" (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_36_ab:
  sectionId (27689)
  sectionNo 36AB
  orderNo 85
  title `Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_ab_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27689&sectionno=36AB&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_36_ab_content:
  string
  line `^1[36AB. Special Courts. --(1) The Central Government, or the State Government, in consultation with`
  line `the Chief Justice of the High Court, shall, for trial of offences relating to adulterated drugs or spurious drugs`
  line `and punishable under clauses (a) and (b) of section 13, sub-section (3) of section 22, clauses (a) and (c) of`
  line `section 27, section 28, section 28A, section 28B and clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 30 and other`
  line `offences relating to adulterated drugs or spurious drugs, by notification, designate one or more Courts of`
  line `Session as a Special Court or Special Courts for such area or areas or for such case or class or group of cases`
  line `as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this sub-section, "High Court" means the High Court of the State in which a`
  line `Court of Session designated as Special Court was functioning immediately before such designation.`
  line
  line `(2) While trying an offence under this Act, a Special Court shall also try an offence, other than an`
  line `offence referred to in sub-section (1), with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_ac:
  sectionId (27690)
  sectionNo 36AC
  orderNo 86
  title `Offences to be cognizable and non-bailable in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_ac_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27690&sectionno=36AC&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_36_ac_content:
  string
  line `^1[36AC. Offences to be cognizable and non-bailable in certain cases. --(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),--`
  line
  line `(a) every offence, relating to adulterated or spurious drug and punishable under clauses (a) and`
  line `(c) of sub-section (1) of section 13, clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 13, sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 22, clauses (a) and (c) of section 27, section 28, section 28A, section 28B and sub-sections`
  line `(1) and (2) of section 30 and other offences relating to adulterated drugs or spurious drugs, shall be`
  line cognizable.
  line
  line `(b) no person accused, of an offence punishable under clauses (a). and (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13, clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 13, sub-section (3) of section 22, clauses (a) and`
  line `(c) of section 27, section 28, section 28A, section 28B and sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 30 and`
  line `other offences relating to adulterated drugs or spurious drugs, shall be released on bail or on his own`
  line `bond unless--`
  line
  line `(i) the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such`
  line `release; and`
  line
  line `(ii) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `commit any offence while on bail:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person, who, is under the age of sixteen years, or is a woman or is sick or infirm, may`
  line `be released on bail, if the Special Court so directs.`
  line
  line `(2) The limitation on granting of bail specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1) is in addition to the`
  line `limitations under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force on granting of bail.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the special powers of the High Court`
  line `regarding bail under section 439 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and the High Court`
  line `may exercise such powers including the power under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of that section as if the`
  line `reference to "Magistrate" in that section includes also a reference to a "Special Court" designated under`
  line `section 36AB.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_ad:
  sectionId (27691)
  sectionNo 36AD
  orderNo 87
  title `Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_ad_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27691&sectionno=36AD&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_36_ad_content:
  string
  line `^1[36AD. Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before Special`
  line `Court. --(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974) (including the provisions as to bails or bonds), shall apply to the proceedings before a`
  line `Special Court and for the purposes of the said provisions, the Special Court shall be deemed to be a`
  line `Court of Session and the person conducting the prosecution before the Special Court, shall be deemed to be`
  line `a Public Prosecutor:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or the State Government may also appoint, for any case or class`
  line `or group of cases, a Special Public Prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified to be appointed as a Public Prosecutor or a Special Public Prosecutor`
  line `under this section unless he has been in practice as an advocate for not less, than seven years, under the Union or`
  line `a State, requiring special knowledge of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person appointed as a Public Prosecutor or a Special Public Prosecutor under this section shall`
  line `be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor within the meaning of clause (u) of section 2 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and the provisions of that Code shall have effect accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_ae:
  sectionId (27692)
  sectionNo 36AE
  orderNo 88
  title `Appeal and revision`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_ae_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-8-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27692&sectionno=36AE&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_36_ae_content:
  string
  line `^1[36AE. Appeal and revision.--The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the`
  line `powers conferred by Chapter XXIX or Chapter XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court of`
  line `Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (27693)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 89
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1955, s. 16, for s. 34.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27693&sectionno=37&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[37. Protection of action taken in good faith.--No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intend to be done under this Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (27694)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 90
  title `Rules to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112&sectionId=27694&sectionno=38&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00023_194023_1523353460112
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[38. Rules to be laid before Parliament.--Every rule made under this Act shall be laid as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions,`
  line `^2[and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree`
  line `that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1964, s. 30 (w.e.f. 15-9-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 68 of 1982, s. 40, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-1983).`
